  description: "multiprocessing.process.BaseProcess.__dict__ lifecycle method membership checks in mprepr159 namespace — BaseProcess.__dict__.__contains__('start')==True (BaseProcess.start() starts the child process; must not be called more than once per process object); BaseProcess.__dict__.__contains__('run')==True (BaseProcess.run() is the method representing the process's activity; it invokes target with args and kwargs); BaseProcess.__dict__.__contains__('join')==True (BaseProcess.join() blocks the calling process until the child process terminates or timeout expires); BaseProcess.__dict__.__contains__('terminate')==True (BaseProcess.terminate() terminates the child process via SIGTERM on Unix); all four are in BaseProcess.__dict__; verified with Python 3.14.3"
